    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>(C) In nomine domini Dei aeterni. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/21">Berengarius </persName><rs key="#Emperor/king"
                        >rex</rs>. Noverit omnium fidelium sanctae Dei Ecclesiae nostrorumque
                        presentium scilicet ac futurorum devota sollertia, <persName
                            key="#Intercessory #Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/216"
                            >Ardingum</persName>
                        <rs key="#Intercessory #Archchancellor #Bishops">reverentissimum episcopum
                            dilectumque archicancellarium nostrum</rs> suppliciter nostrae
                        serenitatis exorasse clementiam, quatenus <rs key="#Hungarians">ob Paganorum
                            incursionem</rs> concede[remus nostra] auctoritate <persName
                            key="#Deacons" ref="#people/227">Audeberto </persName><rs key="#Deacons"
                            >diacono</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Albergaria/gifori #Profits_of_justice #Tolls #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Immunity #Right_to_fortify #Churches #Deacons"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/503"><rs key="#Churches">sanctae Veronensis
                                aecclesiae</rs></orgName> licentiam aedificandi <geogName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Castle #Fluvial_transport #Markets #Profits_of_justice #Right_to_fortify"
                            ref="#estates/116"><rs
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Castle #Right_to_fortify"
                                >castrum</rs><placeName
                                key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Castle #Fluvial_transport #Markets #Profits_of_justice #Right_to_fortify"
                                ref="#places/145"> in loco ubi dicitur [Nogaria]
                            </placeName></geogName>inter <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            ref="#estates/181"><placeName
                                key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                                ref="#places/400"><rs key="#Curtes">curtes </rs>Duorum Roborum
                            </placeName></geogName>et <placeName
                            key="#Villas #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            ref="#places/595"><rs key="#Villas">villam </rs>quae nominatur
                            Tillioano</placeName>, super <rs key="#Rivers">ripam videlicet fluvii
                            qui Tartarum </rs>dic[itur, circa q]uod etiam castrum et infra ipsum
                        castrum <rs key="#Fluvial_transport">negotia</rs> exercere et <rs
                            key="#Markets">mercatum</rs> edificare prefati episcopi precibus
                        licentiam eidem diacono tribuere perpetualiter dignaremur. Cuius dignis
                        impetrationibus acclinati, in prenominato <rs
                            key="#Fundi #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention">loco et
                            fundo</rs> eadem Audebertum diaconum castrum edificare permisimus eumque
                        cum <rs key="#Right_to_fortify">bertiscis, merulorum propugnaculis atque
                            [fossatis omnique monitione et] arg[umento]</rs> affirmare hac
                        inscriptione decrevimus, quatenus ipsum castrum nostra regali fisus
                        auctoritate bertiscis circumdet, propugnaculis muniat, omnique argumento
                        corroboret, et mercatum ibique nostra licentia construat ad suam
                        proprietatem, <rs
                            key="#Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_individuals #Tolls #Teloneum #Rights_of_use_on_woods/pastures/waters #Districtio"
                            >theloneum, palificturam, ripaticum, reddibitiones cunctasque
                            exhibitiones vel districtiones</rs>, sive quicquid per aliquid aut
                        ingenium regie parti exinde aliquando pertinere potuisset prelibato diacono
                        iure [proprieta]rio in integrum concedimus et largimur. nullus quoque comes,
                        vicecomes, sculdassio, gastaldio, decanus vel cuiuslibet dignitatis aut
                        ordinis magna parvaque persona in eodem castro<rs
                            key="#Profits_of_justice #Immunity"> placitum </rs>custodire, aut aliud
                        al[iquid] inibi ad regiam partem exigere vel vindicare, aut <rs
                            key="#Albergaria/gifori #Immunity">mansionatic[a]s </rs>facere
                        potestative presumat, vel de eodem mercato publice parti aliquid persolvere
                        cogatur, sed liceat ei iure proprietario omnia possidere, remota totius
                        potestatis inquietudine vel minoratione. [Cont]ra quod nostrae concessionis
                        preceptum si quis temer[ari]o ausu insurgere temptaverit, ut inchoata
                        per[ficere ne]queat, <rs key="#Penalty">triginta libras auri optimi
                        </rs>solvere cogatur, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">camerae
                            palatii</rs> nostri et medietatem prelibato Audeberto diacono aut cui
                        ipse haec omnia habere concesserit. Quod ut verius credatur et diligentius
                        observetur, manu propria roborantes [anulo] nostro insigniri iussimus.
                        Signum domni (MF) Berengarii serenissimi regis. <persName key="#Chancellor"
                            ref="#people/619">Ambrosius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> ad vicem <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/216">Ardingi</persName>
                        <rs key="#Archchancellor #Bishops">episcopi et archicancellarii
                        </rs>recognovi et subscripsi (SR) (SI n. II) Data non. kal. septemb., anno
                        dominicae incamationis .DCCCCVI., domni vero Berengarii piissimi regis
                        .XVIIII., indictione .VIIII. Actum <placeName key="#Cities" ref="#places/59"
                                ><rs key="#Cities">Veronae.</rs></placeName> in Christi nomine
                        feliciter, a[men]. </ab>
                </div>
